article.headline: S. Dakota St. 82, Texas-Pan American 67
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Kai Williams scored 24 points as South Dakota State snapped a five-game losing streak with an 82-67 win over Texas-Pan American on Saturday. The Jackrabbits (5-15) made nine of their first 16 shots from the field and jumped out to a 23-8 lead over the Broncs. Texas-Pan American (10-10) started slowly, hitting just four of its first 15 shots. The Broncs cut the lead to five points late in the half, but SDSU scored the last four points of the half to take a 37-24 lead. SDSU shot 67 percent from the field and made 20 of 26 free throws in the second half to keep the lead in double figures most of the way. The Broncs shot just 29 percent in the first half and finished the game at 45 percent to 54 percent for SDSU. Garrett Callahan had 15 points for the Jackrabbits. Matt Cadwell added 14 points and Michael Loney had 12 points and six rebounds. SDSU outrebounded the Broncs 35-21. Brian Burrell had 14 points and Danny Puente added 13 for Texas-Pan American.
